  "abstract": "The concept of food security has evolved, developed, multiplied and diversified\r\nsince the first World Food Conference of 1974. There are close to 200 different\r\ndefinitions of the term, but the essence of all these definitions is similar. The most\r\ncommon and useful definition of food security is \"food security exists when all\r\npeople, at all times, have physical. social and economic access to sufficient, safe and\r\nnutritious food which meets their dietary needs and food preferences for an active and\r\nhealthy life....",
